Paper: hep-th/9905185

Date: 1999-05-25

Title: A Speculative Approach to Quantum Gravity

Authors: Paul Federbush (University of Michigan)

Comments: 5 pages, LaTeX

The bare bones of a theory of quantum gravity are exposed. It may have thepotential to solve the cosmological constant problem. Less certain is itsbehavior in the Newtonian limit.